The paper uses deep learning methods to model human categorization of natural images, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of machine learning methods and neural networks suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The study of human behavior and cognition also suggests that it may belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks and models of human behavior suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
